name: cyclopropane-fatty-acyl-phospholipid synthase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + phospholipid olefinic fatty acid = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + phospholipid cyclopropane fatty acid [RN:R03411]
comment: The enzyme adds a methylene group across the 9,10 position of a Delta9-olefinic acyl chain in phosphatidylethanolamine or, more slowly, phosphatidylglycerol or phosphatidylinositol, forming a cyclopropane derivative (cf. EC 2.1.1.16 methylene-fatty-acyl-phospholipid synthase).

references.title: CYCLOPROPANE FATTY ACID SYNTHETASE: PARTIAL PURIFICATION AND PROPERTIES.
Enzymatic synthesis of cyclopropane fatty acids catalyzed by bacterial extracts.
